[SN]TITLE[SN]
Africa this week: Five things we've learnt

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Some of the quirkier snippets from the news in Africa that we did not know last week:

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Shipping executive Jacob Sorensen glided into the Kenyan port of Mombasa, saying that he had made the 1,000km (620-mile) trip along the East African coast to highlight the need to tackle the root causes of piracy. He surfed every day, apart from one stopover in Dar es Salaam, the BBC's Ferdinand Omondi reports.
